summary: Moderately-sized (27 at the moment) collection of RaceMenu presets.
descriptionHtml:
[center][img]http://s5.postimg.org/ll67ipfzr/Myst_Race_Menu.png[/img][/center]

The focus of this project was to offer unique character presets without making them seem out of place in the world of Skyrim. In other words, each one of these characters has its own style, whether it's the playful Arravald or the stern Piermont. Expect this page to be updated fairly regularly with new content.

Note: Screenshots in the description and image section are sorted alphabetically by race.

Feel free to leave a few screenshots or comments. Feedback is welcome and appreciated.


Mods I use (but aren't required):

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/76607/?]Unmasked Faces - no green detailmaps for complexion and necks[/url] - Does as its name implies. Highly recommended.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/35092/?]ApachiiSkyHair natural Retexture[/url] - Better textures for Apachii hair.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/32986/?]Mature Skin[/url] (V2 Beta 10) - Female textures.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/58443/?]Skysight Skins[/url] - Male textures.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/28363/?]Beards[/url] - Beard textures.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/30411/?]Brows[/url] - Brow textures.


Optional

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/7127/?]RANs HeadMesh Variants[/url] - Slimmer faces. Type A or C is what I would recommend. If you use Custom Races you could use a different mesh for each race.


Requirements by preset:

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/24273/?]Ethereal Elven Overhaul[/url] for the elves.
